    "rationale": "All three QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%). Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet required levels. The single shortfall in Test conditions (Gradation 1 vs required Gradation 2) is accepted because ASTM F1717 prescribes a single standardized test configuration for this device class and the regulatory context does not require multi-condition testing for 510(k) clearance. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the submission claim.",
